{"title_page": "Kingdom (manga)", "text_new": "{{Infobox animanga/Header\n| name            = Kingdom\n| image           = Kingdom volume 1.jpg\n| caption         = Cover of the first volume, released in Japan by [[Shueisha]] on May 19, 2006.\n| ja_kanji        = \u30ad\u30f3\u30b0\u30c0\u30e0\n| ja_romaji       = Kingudamu\n| genre           = [[Adventure genre|Adventure]],<ref>{{cite web |title=Kingdom |url=https://www.funimation.com/shows/kingdom/ |publisher=Funimation |accessdate=June 28, 2017}}</ref> [[Historical fiction|historical]],<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2018-04-07/historical-manga-kingdom-gets-live-action-film-project/.130089 |title=Historical Manga Kingdom Gets Live-Action Film Project|website=[[Anime News Network]] |date=April 7, 2018|accessdate=May 28, 2018}}</ref> [[War novel|military]]<ref>{{cite web |last1=Silverman |first1=Rebecca |title=Kingdom DVD - Review |url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/review/kingdom/dvd-the-complete-first-season/.100356 |website=[[Anime News Network]] |accessdate=November 1, 2019 |date=April 8, 2016}}</ref><!-- Note: Use and cite reliable sources to identify genre/s, not personal interpretation. Please don't include more than three genres (per [[MOS:A&M]]). -->\n}}\n{{Infobox animanga/Print\n| type            = manga\n| author          = Yasuhisa Hara\n| publisher       = [[Shueisha]]\n| publisher_en    = \n| demographic     = ''[[Seinen manga|Seinen]]''\n| imprint         = \n| magazine        = [[Weekly Young Jump]]\n| magazine_en     = \n| first           = January 26, 2006\n| last            = \n| volumes         = 57\n| volume_list     = \n}}\n{{Infobox animanga/Video\n| type            = tv series\n| director        = {{ubl|Jun Kamiya {{small|(season 1)}}|Akira Iwanaga {{small|(season 2)}}|Kenichi Imaizumi {{small|(season 3)}}}}\n| producer        = \n| writer          = {{ubl|Naruhisa Arakawa {{small|(seasons 1\u20132)}}|Noboru Takagi {{small|(season 3)}}}}\n| music           = {{ubl|Minako Seki {{small|(seasons 1\u20132)}}|[[Hiroyuki Sawano]] {{small|(season 3)}}|Kohta Yamamoto {{small|(season 3)}}}}\n| studio          = {{ubl|[[Pierrot (company)|Pierrot]] {{small|(seasons 1\u20132)}}|[[Studio Signpost]] {{small|(season 3)}}}}\n| licensee        = {{English anime licensee\n | NA = [[Funimation]]\n}}\n| network         = [[NHK|NHK BS Premium]], [[NHK General TV]]\n| network_en      = \n| first           = June 4, 2012\n| last            =\n| episodes        = 77\n| episode_list    = List of Kingdom (Japanese TV series) episodes\n}}\n{{Infobox animanga/Other\n| title           = Live-action film\n| content         =\n*''[[Kingdom (film)|Kingdom]]'' (2019)\n}}\n{{Infobox animanga/Footer}}\n\n{{Nihongo|'''''Kingdom'''''|\u30ad\u30f3\u30b0\u30c0\u30e0|Kingudamu}} is a Japanese ''[[Seinen manga|seinen]]'' [[manga]] series written and illustrated by Yasuhisa Hara. The manga provides a fictionalized account of the [[Warring States period]] primarily through the experiences of the war orphan [[Li Xin (Qin)|Xin]] and his comrades as he fights to become the greatest general under the heavens, and in doing so, unifying [[China]] for the first time in 500 years. \n\nThe series was adapted into a two-season [[anime]] television series by studio [[Pierrot (company)|Pierrot]]. The first season of 38 episodes aired from June 4, 2012 to February 25, 2013. A second season was announced, and aired for 39 episodes from June 8, 2013 to March 1, 2014. A third season by [[Studio Signpost]] will premiere in April 2020. A [[Kingdom (film)|live-action film]] was released in April 2019.\n\nThe anime has been licensed for an English language release by [[Funimation]].\n\n==Synopsis==\n===Historical context===\nThe story of ''Kingdom'' is a fictional adaptation of the Chinese history period known as the [[Warring States period]], which ended in 221 BC when [[Ying Zheng]], king of Qin, succeeded in [[Qin's wars of unification|conquering the other states]] and unifying China.\n\nSeveral of the characters are based on historical figures. Many times characters will take the names of people in history, and other times they will have completely different names. Oftentimes this is a result of Japanese [[Kanji]] borrowing from Chinese characters, meaning that there are some Chinese names that have no equivalent characters in [[Kanji]]. For example, Ou Ki's (\u738b\u9a0e), name is a slightly altered version of Wang Yi, \u738b\u9f6e, because the last character of his name, \u9f6e, does not exist in Kanji.\n\n===Plot===\nBorn in the [[Warring States period]] of ancient China, Xin and Piao are war-orphans in the kingdom of [[Qin (state)|Qin]] who dream of becoming \"Great Generals of the Heavens\" to rise from their lowly stations in life. One day, however, Piao is taken to the palace by a minister to be used for an unknown purpose, leaving Xin alone as a household slave in a peasant village. A few months later, Piao returns to the village on the verge of death, urging Xin to travel to another village. There he meets a boy who looks nearly identical to Piao, [[Ying Zheng]], the current King of Qin. Xin learns that Piao served as a body double for Ying Zheng, and was mortally wounded in a power struggle for the throne. Though initially furious at Ying Zheng for causing Piao's death, Xin decides to seize the opportunity and aid Ying Zheng in defeating his brother and reclaiming the Qin throne. Successful in this endeavor, Xin officially starts his life as a Qin commander on the battlefields of Warring States China with the goal of becoming the \"Greatest General in the World\", and to help King Zheng of Qin achieve his dream of total unification, ending the incessant warfare once and for all.\n\n==Characters==\n;{{Nihongo|[[Li Xin (Qin)|Li Xin]]|\u674e\u4fe1| Ri Shin}}\n:{{animevoices|[[Masakazu Morita]]|[[Cole Howard (voice actor)|Cole Howard]]}}\n:Xin (Shin in the Japanese version) is an orphan boy who grew up as a servant with his best friend Piao. Xin's behavior is predominantly impulsive, and despite that, he gives courage to the comrades around him. After Piao's death in episode 1, Xin decides to help the King of Qin, Ying Zheng (Ei Sei), escape from his enemies with He Liao Diao. Xin enlists in the State of Qin army soon after, and under Wang Qi (Ou Ki), he is appointed as the leader of the Feixin Unit (Hi Shin Unit), the newly formed 100-Man special unit. Appointing Qiang Lei (Kyou Kai) and Yuan (En) as his lieutenants, Xin joins Wang Qi in his conquest of the State of Zhao Army. During the conflict with the State of Wei, he proclaims to the supreme commander of the Wei Army that he will unify all of China, signifying that his and Ying Zheng's \"paths\" have become interlocked. \n\n;{{Nihongo|[[Ying Zheng]]|\u5b34\u653f|Ei Sei}}\n:{{animevoices|[[Jun Fukuyama]]|[[Micah Solusod]]}}\n:Ying Zheng is the 31st king of the State of Qin. Piao is identical to him, and thus becomes Ying Zheng's double in his escape. He has stated that he will unify all of China, but has only a few years to do so due to the enemies that lay outside of the Qin state (the Zhao, Wie, Chu, and other remaining nations) and internal problems within the country, such as political rivalries with the Queen Dowager and the Royal Harem. Although king, Ying Zheng's power is limited due to the political turmoil with his minister who plans to take the throne. His and Xin's goals became unified when Xin declared that he would be Ying Zheng's \"sword\" in the unification of China. He has a child with the servant woman Xiang (Kou) named Rei.\n\n;{{Nihongo|Piao|\u6f02|Hy\u014d}}\n:{{animevoices|[[Jun Fukuyama]]|}}\n:Xin's childhood best friend and fellow war orphan who also aims to become a general renowned throughout all of China, he is offered a position in the [[Qin (state)|Qin]] palace as Zheng's body double, which he accepts, only to die at the hands of an assassin hired by the Cheng Jiao Faction. Piao is a fictional character created by the author and does not exist in history.\n\n;{{Nihongo|Heliao Diao|\u6cb3\u4e86\u8c82|Kary\u014d Ten}}\n:{{animevoices|[[Rie Kugimiya]]|Shannon Chan-Kent}}\n:He Liao Diao (Ka Ryo Ten) is the last descendant of a mountain tribe who joins Xin in helping Ying Zheng escape from the soldiers chasing him. After witnessing Wang Qi and Xin's war against the Zhao, she (keeping her identity a secret and calling herself a male due to her boyish and childish appearance) is forced to stay at Xin's newly constructed, but poor looking, house. Soon after his return, she states that she will [[Women in ancient warfare|join]] the State of Qin Army but is laughed at. Later in the story, He Liao Diao is taken in as an apprentice of strategic warfare, soon after becoming the strategist for the Feixin Unit. Her first kiss was with Xin, albeit accidentally, and he has groped her several times, also on accident. It is hinted that she has feelings for Xin, however, his relationship with her is seen as a brother-sister one.\n\n;{{Nihongo|Chang Wen Jun|[[:zh:\u660c\u6587\u541b|\u660c\u6587\u541b]]|Sh\u014dbun-kun}}\n:{{animevoices|[[Yutaka Nakano]]|}}\n:A formerly skilled warrior who worked his way up to \u201c[[Chancellor (China)|Chancellor]] of the Left\u201d (chapter 256), a senior adviser of the king. He is shown to be extremely loyal to the Ying Zheng faction, aiding him in both reclaiming the throne and the current in political struggle against L\u00fc Buwei.\n\n;{{Nihongo|Bi|\u58c1|Heki}}\n:{{animevoices|[[Koji Yusa]]|}}\n:Chang Wen Jun's loyal subordinate. At the series start, Heki was a 1000-man commander (chapter 51). By chapter 218, he commands a 1000-man army. Heki is the 3000-man commander in chapter 294. After fighting alongside Xin in many military campaigns, he rises to the rank of General (chapter 372) and is currently seeking greater heights to earn more influence for Ying Zheng (since chapter 51). Xin is shown to rely on him and he has had a crush on Y\u014dtanwa since chapter 22.\n\n;{{Nihongo|Qiang Lei|[[:zh:\u7f8c\u7623|\u7f8c\u7623]]|Ky\u014d Kai}}\n:{{animevoices|[[Y\u014dko Hikasa]]|}}\n:Qiang Lei (Kyou Kai) is a former heir to the Shi Y\u016b ([[Chi You]]), an assassin group with barbaric traditions used to cultivate strong assassins at the expense of killing undesirable candidates. After the death of her sister, Qiang Xiang (Kyou Shou),  in one of these traditions, Qiang Lei vowed revenge against the woman who had killed her. She joined the Feixin Unit (as a young boy, keeping her sex a secret like He Liao Diao) after its formation and became a vice commander, despite the fact that she is stronger and smarter than Xin (as shown by her power and the fact that she created the strategies for them). She reveals her identity to Xin and becomes more friendly and open towards he alone before finally accepting her place in the unit and calling it her home. She may have feelings for Xin which have been hinted at on many occasions, one being her confession of wanting to have a child with him (she did not know about intercourse at the time).\n\n==Media==\n===Manga===\n''Kingdom'' is written and illustrated by Yasuhisa Hara and originated from two one-shots he drew on Li Mu and Meng Wu. The manga debuted in the 9th issue of [[Shueisha]]'s ''[[Weekly Young Jump]]'' [[seinen manga|''seinen'' manga]] magazine on January 26, 2006.<ref>{{cite web |script-title=ja:\u5b9f\u5199\u300e\u30ad\u30f3\u30b0\u30c0\u30e0\u300f\u306b\u5c71\ufa11\u8ce2\u4eba\u3001\u5409\u6ca2\u4eae\u3001\u9577\u6fa4\u307e\u3055\u307f\u3001\u6a4b\u672c\u74b0\u5948\u3089\u8c6a\u83ef\u30ad\u30e3\u30b9\u30c8\u96c6\u7d50\uff01\u914d\u5f79\u660e\u3089\u304b\u306b |url=https://eigaland.com/topics/?p=87565 |website=Eigaland |accessdate=December 5, 2018 |language=Japanese |date=October 9, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |script-title=ja:2006\u5e74 |url=http://youngjump.jp/history/2006.html |website=youngjump.jp |publisher=[[Shueisha]] |accessdate=July 22, 2019 |language=ja}}</ref> The first ''[[tank\u014dbon]]'' volume was released by [[Shueisha]] on May 19, 2006.<ref>{{cite web |script-title=ja:\u30ad\u30f3\u30b0\u30c0\u30e0 1 |url=http://books.shueisha.co.jp/items/contents.html?isbn=4-08-877079-X |publisher=[[Shueisha]] |accessdate=December 5, 2018 |language=Japanese}}</ref> As of November 2019, fifty-six ''tank\u014dbon'' volumes have been released.<ref>{{cite web |script-title=ja:\u30ad\u30f3\u30b0\u30c0\u30e0 56 |url=https://books.shueisha.co.jp/items/contents.html?isbn=978-4-08-891402-2 |publisher=[[Shueisha]] |accessdate=December 30, 2019 |language=Japanese}}</ref>\n\nIn 2015, Hara stated that he has planned to extend the series up to 100 volumes.<ref>{{cite web |title=Kingdom Manga Creator Considers Ending Series at 100 Volumes |url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2015-10-07/kingdom-manga-creator-considers-ending-series-at-100-volumes/.93888 |website=[[Anime News Network]] |accessdate=August 19, 2018 |date=October 8, 2015}}</ref>\n\n===Anime===\n{{see also|List of Kingdom (Japanese TV series) episodes}}\nAn [[anime]] television series was adapted by studio [[Pierrot (company)|Pierrot]]. Two seasons of seventy-seven episodes were produced. The first season which consisted of thirty-eight episodes aired from June 4, 2012 to February 25, 2013 on NHK BS Premium. A second season aired thirty-nine episodes from June 8, 2013 to March 1, 2014.<ref name=\"season 2\">{{cite web|title=\u30a2\u30cb\u30e1\u300c\u30ad\u30f3\u30b0\u30c0\u30e0\u300d\u7b2c2\u30b7\u30ea\u30fc\u30ba\u5236\u4f5c\u6c7a\u5b9a!6\u6708\u3088\u308a\u958b\u59cb|website=[[Natalie (website)|Natalie]]|url=http://natalie.mu/comic/news/83619|language=Japanese|access-date=January 1, 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2014-02-18/kingdom-2nd-anime-series-to-end-on-march-1 |title=Kingdom's 2nd Anime Series to End on March 1|website=[[Anime News Network]] |date=February 18, 2014|accessdate=February 18, 2020}}</ref> The anime has been licensed for an English language release by [[Funimation]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Funimation acquisition |website=[[Anime News Network]]|url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/press-release/2012-06-08/funimation-entertainment-announces-new-acquisition-simulcast-at-animenext|accessdate=April 29, 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Ressler |first1=Karen |title=Kingdom Anime Season 1 Gets DVD Release With English Dub |url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2015-10-16/kingdom-anime-season-1-gets-dvd-release-with-english-dub/.94266 |website=[[Anime News Network]] |accessdate=November 23, 2019 |date=October 16, 2015}}</ref>\n\nA third season has been announced along with brand new staff members. It is set to premiere on [[NHK General TV]](NHK-G) on April 5, 2020.<ref>{{cite web |author1=Patrick Frye |title=Kingdom Season 3 release date confirmed for spring 2020 |url=https://www.monstersandcritics.com/anime/kingdom-season-3-release-date-2020-kingdom-manga-coalition-invasion-story-arc/ |website=[[Monsters and Critics]] |accessdate=February 14, 2020 |date=February 14, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |author1=Rafael Antonio Pineda |title=Kingdom Gets 3rd TV Anime Series With Brand New Staff in April |url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2019-11-07/kingdom-gets-3rd-tv-anime-series-with-brand-new-staff-in-april/.153068 |website=[[Anime News Network]] |accessdate=November 8, 2019 |date=November 7, 2019}}</ref> The creator has confirmed that the third season will cover the Coalition Invasion arc.<ref>{{cite web |author1=Patrick Frye |title=Kingdom Season 3 release date confirmed for 2020: Kingdom manga\u2019s Coalition Invasion arc compared to the anime |url=https://www.monstersandcritics.com/anime/kingdom-season-3-release-date-2020-kingdom-manga-coalition-invasion-story-arc/ |website=[[Monsters and Critics]] |accessdate=November 8, 2019 |date=November 8, 2019}}</ref> The series third season will have Kenichi Imaizumi directing at Pierrot's subsidiary company [[Studio Signpost]], with scripts by Noboru Takagi and character designs by Hisashi Abe.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2019-12-15/kingdom-anime-season-3-reveals-new-staff-visual/.154399|title= 'Kingdom' Anime Season 3 Reveals New Staff, Visua|website= [[Anime News Network]]|author= Antonio Pineda, Rafael|date= December 15, 2019|accessdate= December 15, 2019}}</ref> [[Hiroyuki Sawano]] and Kohta Yamamoto are composing the music.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://kingdom-anime.com/staffcast/|title=Staff & Cast|website=Kingdom|accessdate=January 6, 2020|language=Japanese}}</ref>\n\n===Film===\n{{main|Kingdom (film)}}\nOn April 17, 2016, a special short movie was released by the manga's publishing magazine ''Weekly Young Jump''. It is a live action promotional short film for the series. It was made for the 10th Anniversary of Kingdom's release and filmed by Hengdian World Studios in China. In April 2018, Kingdom's creator Yasuhira Hara previously revealed that a full-length live-action film of his series had been green-lit. The author stated he took part in script meetings, praising the 'satisfying' screenplay, the 'unprecedented' budget, and everyone in the 'ultra-grand' casts, starring [[Kento Yamazaki]] and Directed by [[Shinsuke Sato]].<ref>https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=uvG5e5Nb__U</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Chapman |first1=Paul |title=\"Kingdom\" Manga Celebrates 10th Anniversary with Live-Action Project |url=https://www.crunchyroll.com/es/anime-news/2016/04/11-1/kingdom-manga-celebrates-10th-anniversary-with-live-action-project |website=[[Crunchyroll]] |accessdate=April 4, 2019 |date=April 11, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://comicbook.com/anime/2018/04/17/kingdom-live-action-movie-cast-announced/|title= ''Kingdom'' Live Action Movie Cast Announced|website= ComicBook|date= April 17, 2018}}</ref> The film was released on April 19, 2019.<ref>{{Citeweb |url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2018-10-09/live-action-kingdom-film-unveils-cast-director-april-19-opening/.137904|title= Live Action ''Kingdom'' Film Unveils Cast, Director, April 19 Opening|website= [[AnimeNewsNetwork]]|date= October 8, 2018|accessdate= October 8, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Citeweb |url=https://variety.com/2018/film/asia/sony-unveils-japan-china-manga-adaptation-kingdom-1202973451/|title= SPEJ and Square Enix Unveils China-Set Manga Adaptation \"Kingdom\"!|website= [[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|date= October 8, 2018|accessdate= October 8, 2018}}</ref>\n\n===Video games===\nA [[PlayStation Portable]] [[beat 'em up]] styled video game was released on November 25, 2010 entitled ''Kingdom Ikki Tousen No Tsurugi''.<ref>{{cite web|title=Kingdom: Ikki Tousen no Tsurugi|publisher=[[GameSpot]]|url=http://www.gamespot.com/kingdom-ikki-tousen-no-tsurugi/reviews/|accessdate=May 15, 2014}}</ref> The game was released only in Japan.\n\nA free-to-play mobile game called ''Kingdom: Seven Flags'' was released on October 24, 2016 in Japan.<ref>{{cite web|title=Bandai Namco announces Kingdom: Seven Flags for smartphones|publisher=Gematsu|url=http://gematsu.com/2016/08/bandai-namco-announces-kingdom-seven-flags-smartphones|last=Romano|first=Sal|date=August 24, 2016|accessdate=November 29, 2017}}</ref>\n\nA free-to-play mobile game called ''Kingdom Ran'' was released in 2018.\n\n==Reception==\nThe series had over 30 million copies in print as of April 2017,<ref>{{cite web|last=Pineda|first=Rafael Antonio|url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/daily-briefs/2017-04-06/yasuhisa-hara-kingdom-manga-has-30-million-copies-in-print/.114382|title=Yasuhisa Hara's Kingdom Manga Has 30 Million Copies in Print|website=[[Anime News Network]]|date=April 6, 2017|accessdate=April 7, 2017}}</ref> 38 million copies in print as of December 2018,<ref>{{cite web|last=Hodgkins|first=Crystalyn|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2019-01-01/roundup-of-newly-revealed-print-counts-for-manga-light-novel-series-december-2018/.141402|title=Roundup of Newly Revealed Print Counts for Manga, Light Novel Series - December 2018|website=[[Anime News Network]]|date=January 1, 2019|accessdate=April 4, 2019}}</ref> and over 47 million copies in print as of November 2019.<ref>{{cite web |script-title=ja:\u300c\u30ad\u30f3\u30b0\u30c0\u30e0\u300d\u6700\u65b056\u5dfb\u767a\u58f2\u3000\u57fa\u5c71\u753a\u51fa\u8eab\u30fb\u539f\u6cf0\u4e45\u3055\u3093\u306e\u4eba\u6c17\u6f2b\u753b |url=http://www.saga-s.co.jp/articles/-/455822 |website=Saga Shimbun |accessdate=November 21, 2019 |language=ja |date=November 19, 2019}}</ref> ''Kingdom'' was the 3rd best selling manga in 2019.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Loo |first1=Egan |title=Top-Selling Manga in Japan by Series: 2019 |url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2019-11-27/top-selling-manga-in-japan-by-series-2019/.153758 |website=[[Anime News Network]] |accessdate=November 28, 2019 |date=November 27, 2019}}</ref>\n\n''Kingdom'' was the grand prize winner for the [[Tezuka Osamu Cultural Prize]] in 2013 with one judge commenting, \"I can't remember the last time I read nearly 30 volumes (of a manga title) in a row feeling this excited.\"<ref>{{cite web|title=Tezuka Osamu Prize Winners |publisher=[[Asahi Shimbun]] |url=http://ajw.asahi.com/article/cool_japan/style/AJ201305090011 |accessdate=April 28, 2014 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140429185007/http://ajw.asahi.com/article/cool_japan/style/AJ201305090011 |archivedate=April 29, 2014 }}</ref> In 2019, ''Kingdom'' ranked 1st on the 19th \"Book of the Year\" list by ''Da Vinci'' magazine.<ref>{{cite web |author1=Rafael Antonio Pineda |title=Kingdom Manga Tops Da Vinci Ranking |url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2019-12-06/kingdom-manga-tops-da-vinci-ranking/.154037 |website=[[Anime News Network]] |accessdate=December 6, 2019 |date=December 6, 2019}}</ref>\n\nThe manga earned a Guinness World Record on December 12, 2012 for Manga written by the most people. The record was due to its \"Social Kingdom\" campaign in which fans and other artists were given the task of redrawing the entire 26th volume. Participants included manga creators [[Eiichiro Oda]] (''[[One Piece]]''), [[Masashi Kishimoto]] (''[[Naruto]]''), [[Hirohiko Araki]] (''[[JoJo's Bizarre Adventure]]''), as well as voice actors and fans.<ref>{{cite web|title=Kingdom wins Guinness World Record |publisher=[[Asahi Shimbun]] |url=http://ajw.asahi.com/article/cool_japan/anime_news/AJ201212310022 |accessdate=April 28, 2014 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140429201955/http://ajw.asahi.com/article/cool_japan/anime_news/AJ201212310022 |archivedate=April 29, 2014 }}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{Official website|http://www9.nhk.or.jp/anime/kingdom/|Official anime website}} {{in lang|ja}}\n* {{Ann|manga|11117|Kingdom}}\n\n{{Series in Weekly Young Jump}}\n{{Weekly Young Jump - 2000\u20132009}}\n{{Tezuka Osamu Cultural Prize}}\n{{Pierrot (company)}}\n{{Studio Signpost}}\n\n[[Category:2012 anime television series]]\n[[Category:2013 anime television series]]\n[[Category:2020 anime television series]]\n[[Category:Upcoming anime television series]]\n[[Category:Adventure anime and manga]]\n[[Category:Anime series based on manga]]\n[[Category:Funimation]]\n[[Category:Historical anime and manga]]\n[[Category:Manga adapted into films]]\n[[Category:NHK shows]]\n[[Category:Pierrot (company)]]\n[[Category:Seinen manga]]\n[[Category:Shueisha franchises]]\n[[Category:Shueisha manga]]\n[[Category:Studio Signpost]]\n[[Category:Television series set in the Zhou dynasty]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox animanga/Header\n| name            = Kingdom\n| image           = Kingdom volume 1.jpg\n| caption         = Cover of the first volume, released in Japan by [[Shueisha]] on May 19, 2006.\n| ja_kanji        = \u30ad\u30f3\u30b0\u30c0\u30e0\n| ja_romaji       = Kingudamu\n| genre           = [[Adventure genre|Adventure]],<ref>{{cite web |title=Kingdom |url=https://www.funimation.com/shows/kingdom/ |publisher=Funimation |accessdate=June 28, 2017}}</ref> [[Historical fiction|historical]],<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2018-04-07/historical-manga-kingdom-gets-live-action-film-project/.130089 |title=Historical Manga Kingdom Gets Live-Action Film Project|website=[[Anime News Network]] |date=April 7, 2018|accessdate=May 28, 2018}}</ref> [[War novel|military]]<ref>{{cite web |last1=Silverman |first1=Rebecca |title=Kingdom DVD - Review |url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/review/kingdom/dvd-the-complete-first-season/.100356 |website=[[Anime News Network]] |accessdate=November 1, 2019 |date=April 8, 2016}}</ref><!-- Note: Use and cite reliable sources to identify genre/s, not personal interpretation. Please don't include more than three genres (per [[MOS:A&M]]). -->\n}}\n{{Infobox animanga/Print\n| type            = manga\n| author          = Yasuhisa Hara\n| publisher       = [[Shueisha]]\n| publisher_en    = \n| demographic     = ''[[Seinen manga|Seinen]]''\n| imprint         = \n| magazine        = [[Weekly Young Jump]]\n| magazine_en     = \n| first           = January 26, 2006\n| last            = \n| volumes         = 57\n| volume_list     = \n}}\n{{Infobox animanga/Video\n| type            = tv series\n| director        = {{ubl|Jun Kamiya {{small|(season 1)}}|Akira Iwanaga {{small|(season 2)}}|Kenichi Imaizumi {{small|(season 3)}}}}\n| producer        = \n| writer          = {{ubl|Naruhisa Arakawa {{small|(seasons 1\u20132)}}|Noboru Takagi {{small|(season 3)}}}}\n| music           = {{ubl|Minako Seki {{small|(seasons 1\u20132)}}|[[Hiroyuki Sawano]] {{small|(season 3)}}|Kohta Yamamoto {{small|(season 3)}}}}\n| studio          = {{ubl|[[Pierrot (company)|Pierrot]] {{small|(seasons 1\u20132)}}|[[Studio Signpost]] {{small|(season 3)}}}}\n| licensee        = {{English anime licensee\n | NA = [[Funimation]]\n}}\n| network         = [[NHK|NHK BS Premium]], [[NHK General TV]]\n| network_en      = \n| first           = June 4, 2012\n| last            =\n| episodes        = 77\n| episode_list    = List of Kingdom (Japanese TV series) episodes\n}}\n{{Infobox animanga/Other\n| title           = Live-action film\n| content         =\n*''[[Kingdom (film)|Kingdom]]'' (2019)\n}}\n{{Infobox animanga/Footer}}\n\n{{Nihongo|'''''Kingdom'''''|\u30ad\u30f3\u30b0\u30c0\u30e0|Kingudamu}} is a Japanese ''[[Seinen manga|seinen]]'' [[manga]] series written and illustrated by Yasuhisa Hara. The manga provides a fictionalized account of the [[Warring States period]] primarily through the experiences of the war orphan [[Li Xin (Qin)|Xin]] and his comrades as he fights to become the greatest general under the heavens, and in doing so, unifying [[China]] for the first time in 500 years. \n\nThe series was adapted into a two-season [[anime]] television series by studio [[Pierrot (company)|Pierrot]]. The first season of 38 episodes aired from June 4, 2012 to February 25, 2013. A second season was announced, and aired for 39 episodes from June 8, 2013 to March 1, 2014. A third season by [[Studio Signpost]] will premiere in April 2020. A [[Kingdom (film)|live-action film]] was released in April 2019.\n\nThe anime has been licensed for an English language release by [[Funimation]].\n\n==Synopsis==\n===Historical context===\nThe story of ''Kingdom'' is a fictional adaptation of the Chinese history period known as the [[Warring States period]], which ended in 221 BC when [[Ying Zheng]], king of Qin, succeeded in [[Qin's wars of unification|conquering the other states]] and unifying China.\n\nSeveral of the characters are based on historical figures. Many times characters will take the names of people in history, and other times they will have completely different names. Oftentimes this is a result of Japanese [[Kanji]] borrowing from Chinese characters, meaning that there are some Chinese names that have no equivalent characters in [[Kanji]]. For example, Ou Ki's (\u738b\u9a0e), name is a slightly altered version of Wang Yi, \u738b\u9f6e, because the last character of his name, \u9f6e, does not exist in Kanji.\n\n===Plot===\nBorn in the [[Warring States period]] of ancient China, Xin and Piao are war-orphans in the kingdom of [[Qin (state)|Qin]] who dream of becoming \"Great Generals of the Heavens\" to rise from their lowly stations in life. One day, however, Piao is taken to the palace by a minister to be used for an unknown purpose, leaving Xin alone as a household slave in a peasant village. A few months later, Piao returns to the village on the verge of death, urging Xin to travel to another village. There he meets a boy who looks nearly identical to Piao, [[Ying Zheng]], the current King of Qin. Xin learns that Piao served as a body double for Ying Zheng, and was mortally wounded in a power struggle for the throne. Though initially furious at Ying Zheng for causing Piao's death, Xin decides to seize the opportunity and aid Ying Zheng in defeating his brother and reclaiming the Qin throne. Successful in this endeavor, Xin officially starts his life as a Qin commander on the battlefields of Warring States China with the goal of becoming the \"Greatest General in the World\", and to help King Zheng of Qin achieve his dream of total unification, ending the incessant warfare once and for all.\n\n==Characters==\n;{{Nihongo|[[Li Xin (Qin)|Li Xin]]|\u674e\u4fe1| Ri Shin}}\n:{{animevoices|[[Masakazu Morita]]|[[Cole Howard (voice actor)|Cole Howard]]}}\n:Xin (Shin in the Japanese version) is an orphan boy who grew up as a servant with his best friend Piao. Xin's behavior is predominantly impulsive, and despite that, he gives courage to the comrades around him. After Piao's death in episode 1, Xin decides to help the King of Qin, Ying Zheng (Ei Sei), escape from his enemies with He Liao Diao. Xin enlists in the State of Qin army soon after, and under Wang Qi (Ou Ki), he is appointed as the leader of the Feixin Unit (Hi Shin Unit), the newly formed 100-Man special unit. Appointing Qiang Lei (Kyou Kai) and Yuan (En) as his lieutenants, Xin joins Wang Qi in his conquest of the State of Zhao Army. During the conflict with the State of Wei, he proclaims to the supreme commander of the Wei Army that he will unify all of China, signifying that his and Ying Zheng's \"paths\" have become interlocked. \n\n;{{Nihongo|[[Ying Zheng]]|\u5b34\u653f|Ei Sei}}\n:{{animevoices|[[Jun Fukuyama]]|Micah Solusod}}\n:Ying Zheng is the 31st king of the State of Qin. Piao is identical to him, and thus becomes Ying Zheng's double in his escape. He has stated that he will unify all of China, but has only a few years to do so due to the enemies that lay outside of the Qin state (the Zhao, Wie, Chu, and other remaining nations) and internal problems within the country, such as political rivalries with the Queen Dowager and the Royal Harem. Although king, Ying Zheng's power is limited due to the political turmoil with his minister who plans to take the throne. His and Xin's goals became unified when Xin declared that he would be Ying Zheng's \"sword\" in the unification of China. He has a child with the servant woman Xiang (Kou) named Rei.\n\n;{{Nihongo|Piao|\u6f02|Hy\u014d}}\n:{{animevoices|[[Jun Fukuyama]]|}}\n:Xin's childhood best friend and fellow war orphan who also aims to become a general renowned throughout all of China, he is offered a position in the [[Qin (state)|Qin]] palace as Zheng's body double, which he accepts, only to die at the hands of an assassin hired by the Cheng Jiao Faction. Piao is a fictional character created by the author and does not exist in history.\n\n;{{Nihongo|Heliao Diao|\u6cb3\u4e86\u8c82|Kary\u014d Ten}}\n:{{animevoices|[[Rie Kugimiya]]|Shannon Chan-Kent}}\n:He Liao Diao (Ka Ryo Ten) is the last descendant of a mountain tribe who joins Xin in helping Ying Zheng escape from the soldiers chasing him. After witnessing Wang Qi and Xin's war against the Zhao, she (keeping her identity a secret and calling herself a male due to her boyish and childish appearance) is forced to stay at Xin's newly constructed, but poor looking, house. Soon after his return, she states that she will [[Women in ancient warfare|join]] the State of Qin Army but is laughed at. Later in the story, He Liao Diao is taken in as an apprentice of strategic warfare, soon after becoming the strategist for the Feixin Unit. Her first kiss was with Xin, albeit accidentally, and he has groped her several times, also on accident. It is hinted that she has feelings for Xin, however, his relationship with her is seen as a brother-sister one.\n\n;{{Nihongo|Chang Wen Jun|[[:zh:\u660c\u6587\u541b|\u660c\u6587\u541b]]|Sh\u014dbun-kun}}\n:{{animevoices|Nakano Yutaka|}}\n:A formerly skilled warrior who worked his way up to \u201c[[Chancellor (China)|Chancellor]] of the Left\u201d (chapter 256), a senior adviser of the king. He is shown to be extremely loyal to the Ying Zheng faction, aiding him in both reclaiming the throne and the current in political struggle against L\u00fc Buwei.\n\n;{{Nihongo|Bi|\u58c1|Heki}}\n:{{animevoices|[[Koji Yusa]]|}}\n:Chang Wen Jun's loyal subordinate. At the series start, Heki was a 1000-man commander (chapter 51). By chapter 218, he commands a 1000-man army. Heki is the 3000-man commander in chapter 294. After fighting alongside Xin in many military campaigns, he rises to the rank of General (chapter 372) and is currently seeking greater heights to earn more influence for Ying Zheng (since chapter 51). Xin is shown to rely on him and he has had a crush on Y\u014dtanwa since chapter 22.\n\n;{{Nihongo|Qiang Lei|[[:zh:\u7f8c\u7623|\u7f8c\u7623]]|Ky\u014d Kai}}\n:{{animevoices|[[Hikasa Yoko]]|}}\n:Qiang Lei (Kyou Kai) is a former heir to the Shi Y\u016b ([[Chi You]]), an assassin group with barbaric traditions used to cultivate strong assassins at the expense of killing undesirable candidates. After the death of her sister, Qiang Xiang (Kyou Shou),  in one of these traditions, Qiang Lei vowed revenge against the woman who had killed her. She joined the Feixin Unit (as a young boy, keeping her sex a secret like He Liao Diao) after its formation and became a vice commander, despite the fact that she is stronger and smarter than Xin (as shown by her power and the fact that she created the strategies for them). She reveals her identity to Xin and becomes more friendly and open towards he alone before finally accepting her place in the unit and calling it her home. She may have feelings for Xin which have been hinted at on many occasions, one being her confession of wanting to have a child with him (she did not know about intercourse at the time).\n\n==Media==\n===Manga===\n''Kingdom'' is written and illustrated by Yasuhisa Hara and originated from two one-shots he drew on Li Mu and Meng Wu. The manga debuted in the 9th issue of [[Shueisha]]'s ''[[Weekly Young Jump]]'' [[seinen manga|''seinen'' manga]] magazine on January 26, 2006.<ref>{{cite web |script-title=ja:\u5b9f\u5199\u300e\u30ad\u30f3\u30b0\u30c0\u30e0\u300f\u306b\u5c71\ufa11\u8ce2\u4eba\u3001\u5409\u6ca2\u4eae\u3001\u9577\u6fa4\u307e\u3055\u307f\u3001\u6a4b\u672c\u74b0\u5948\u3089\u8c6a\u83ef\u30ad\u30e3\u30b9\u30c8\u96c6\u7d50\uff01\u914d\u5f79\u660e\u3089\u304b\u306b |url=https://eigaland.com/topics/?p=87565 |website=Eigaland |accessdate=December 5, 2018 |language=Japanese |date=October 9, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |script-title=ja:2006\u5e74 |url=http://youngjump.jp/history/2006.html |website=youngjump.jp |publisher=[[Shueisha]] |accessdate=July 22, 2019 |language=ja}}</ref> The first ''[[tank\u014dbon]]'' volume was released by [[Shueisha]] on May 19, 2006.<ref>{{cite web |script-title=ja:\u30ad\u30f3\u30b0\u30c0\u30e0 1 |url=http://books.shueisha.co.jp/items/contents.html?isbn=4-08-877079-X |publisher=[[Shueisha]] |accessdate=December 5, 2018 |language=Japanese}}</ref> As of November 2019, fifty-six ''tank\u014dbon'' volumes have been released.<ref>{{cite web |script-title=ja:\u30ad\u30f3\u30b0\u30c0\u30e0 56 |url=https://books.shueisha.co.jp/items/contents.html?isbn=978-4-08-891402-2 |publisher=[[Shueisha]] |accessdate=December 30, 2019 |language=Japanese}}</ref>\n\nIn 2015, Hara stated that he has planned to extend the series up to 100 volumes.<ref>{{cite web |title=Kingdom Manga Creator Considers Ending Series at 100 Volumes |url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2015-10-07/kingdom-manga-creator-considers-ending-series-at-100-volumes/.93888 |website=[[Anime News Network]] |accessdate=August 19, 2018 |date=October 8, 2015}}</ref>\n\n===Anime===\n{{see also|List of Kingdom (Japanese TV series) episodes}}\nAn [[anime]] television series was adapted by studio [[Pierrot (company)|Pierrot]]. Two seasons of seventy-seven episodes were produced. The first season which consisted of thirty-eight episodes aired from June 4, 2012 to February 25, 2013 on NHK BS Premium. A second season aired thirty-nine episodes from June 8, 2013 to March 1, 2014.<ref name=\"season 2\">{{cite web|title=\u30a2\u30cb\u30e1\u300c\u30ad\u30f3\u30b0\u30c0\u30e0\u300d\u7b2c2\u30b7\u30ea\u30fc\u30ba\u5236\u4f5c\u6c7a\u5b9a!6\u6708\u3088\u308a\u958b\u59cb|website=[[Natalie (website)|Natalie]]|url=http://natalie.mu/comic/news/83619|language=Japanese|access-date=January 1, 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2014-02-18/kingdom-2nd-anime-series-to-end-on-march-1 |title=Kingdom's 2nd Anime Series to End on March 1|website=[[Anime News Network]] |date=February 18, 2014|accessdate=February 18, 2020}}</ref> The anime has been licensed for an English language release by [[Funimation]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Funimation acquisition |website=[[Anime News Network]]|url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/press-release/2012-06-08/funimation-entertainment-announces-new-acquisition-simulcast-at-animenext|accessdate=April 29, 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Ressler |first1=Karen |title=Kingdom Anime Season 1 Gets DVD Release With English Dub |url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2015-10-16/kingdom-anime-season-1-gets-dvd-release-with-english-dub/.94266 |website=[[Anime News Network]] |accessdate=November 23, 2019 |date=October 16, 2015}}</ref>\n\nA third season has been announced along with brand new staff members. It is set to premiere on [[NHK General TV]](NHK-G) on April 5, 2020.<ref>{{cite web |author1=Patrick Frye |title=Kingdom Season 3 release date confirmed for spring 2020 |url=https://www.monstersandcritics.com/anime/kingdom-season-3-release-date-2020-kingdom-manga-coalition-invasion-story-arc/ |website=[[Monsters and Critics]] |accessdate=February 14, 2020 |date=February 14, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |author1=Rafael Antonio Pineda |title=Kingdom Gets 3rd TV Anime Series With Brand New Staff in April |url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2019-11-07/kingdom-gets-3rd-tv-anime-series-with-brand-new-staff-in-april/.153068 |website=[[Anime News Network]] |accessdate=November 8, 2019 |date=November 7, 2019}}</ref> The creator has confirmed that the third season will cover the Coalition Invasion arc.<ref>{{cite web |author1=Patrick Frye |title=Kingdom Season 3 release date confirmed for 2020: Kingdom manga\u2019s Coalition Invasion arc compared to the anime |url=https://www.monstersandcritics.com/anime/kingdom-season-3-release-date-2020-kingdom-manga-coalition-invasion-story-arc/ |website=[[Monsters and Critics]] |accessdate=November 8, 2019 |date=November 8, 2019}}</ref> The series third season will have Kenichi Imaizumi directing at Pierrot's subsidiary company [[Studio Signpost]], with scripts by Noboru Takagi and character designs by Hisashi Abe.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2019-12-15/kingdom-anime-season-3-reveals-new-staff-visual/.154399|title= 'Kingdom' Anime Season 3 Reveals New Staff, Visua|website= [[Anime News Network]]|author= Antonio Pineda, Rafael|date= December 15, 2019|accessdate= December 15, 2019}}</ref> [[Hiroyuki Sawano]] and Kohta Yamamoto are composing the music.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://kingdom-anime.com/staffcast/|title=Staff & Cast|website=Kingdom|accessdate=January 6, 2020|language=Japanese}}</ref>\n\n===Film===\n{{main|Kingdom (film)}}\nOn April 17, 2016, a special short movie was released by the manga's publishing magazine ''Weekly Young Jump''. It is a live action promotional short film for the series. It was made for the 10th Anniversary of Kingdom's release and filmed by Hengdian World Studios in China. In April 2018, Kingdom's creator Yasuhira Hara previously revealed that a full-length live-action film of his series had been green-lit. The author stated he took part in script meetings, praising the 'satisfying' screenplay, the 'unprecedented' budget, and everyone in the 'ultra-grand' casts, starring [[Kento Yamazaki]] and Directed by [[Shinsuke Sato]].<ref>https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=uvG5e5Nb__U</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Chapman |first1=Paul |title=\"Kingdom\" Manga Celebrates 10th Anniversary with Live-Action Project |url=https://www.crunchyroll.com/es/anime-news/2016/04/11-1/kingdom-manga-celebrates-10th-anniversary-with-live-action-project |website=[[Crunchyroll]] |accessdate=April 4, 2019 |date=April 11, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://comicbook.com/anime/2018/04/17/kingdom-live-action-movie-cast-announced/|title= ''Kingdom'' Live Action Movie Cast Announced|website= ComicBook|date= April 17, 2018}}</ref> The film was released on April 19, 2019.<ref>{{Citeweb |url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2018-10-09/live-action-kingdom-film-unveils-cast-director-april-19-opening/.137904|title= Live Action ''Kingdom'' Film Unveils Cast, Director, April 19 Opening|website= [[AnimeNewsNetwork]]|date= October 8, 2018|accessdate= October 8, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Citeweb |url=https://variety.com/2018/film/asia/sony-unveils-japan-china-manga-adaptation-kingdom-1202973451/|title= SPEJ and Square Enix Unveils China-Set Manga Adaptation \"Kingdom\"!|website= [[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|date= October 8, 2018|accessdate= October 8, 2018}}</ref>\n\n===Video games===\nA [[PlayStation Portable]] [[beat 'em up]] styled video game was released on November 25, 2010 entitled ''Kingdom Ikki Tousen No Tsurugi''.<ref>{{cite web|title=Kingdom: Ikki Tousen no Tsurugi|publisher=[[GameSpot]]|url=http://www.gamespot.com/kingdom-ikki-tousen-no-tsurugi/reviews/|accessdate=May 15, 2014}}</ref> The game was released only in Japan.\n\nA free-to-play mobile game called ''Kingdom: Seven Flags'' was released on October 24, 2016 in Japan.<ref>{{cite web|title=Bandai Namco announces Kingdom: Seven Flags for smartphones|publisher=Gematsu|url=http://gematsu.com/2016/08/bandai-namco-announces-kingdom-seven-flags-smartphones|last=Romano|first=Sal|date=August 24, 2016|accessdate=November 29, 2017}}</ref>\n\nA free-to-play mobile game called ''Kingdom Ran'' was released in 2018.\n\n==Reception==\nThe series had over 30 million copies in print as of April 2017,<ref>{{cite web|last=Pineda|first=Rafael Antonio|url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/daily-briefs/2017-04-06/yasuhisa-hara-kingdom-manga-has-30-million-copies-in-print/.114382|title=Yasuhisa Hara's Kingdom Manga Has 30 Million Copies in Print|website=[[Anime News Network]]|date=April 6, 2017|accessdate=April 7, 2017}}</ref> 38 million copies in print as of December 2018,<ref>{{cite web|last=Hodgkins|first=Crystalyn|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2019-01-01/roundup-of-newly-revealed-print-counts-for-manga-light-novel-series-december-2018/.141402|title=Roundup of Newly Revealed Print Counts for Manga, Light Novel Series - December 2018|website=[[Anime News Network]]|date=January 1, 2019|accessdate=April 4, 2019}}</ref> and over 47 million copies in print as of November 2019.<ref>{{cite web |script-title=ja:\u300c\u30ad\u30f3\u30b0\u30c0\u30e0\u300d\u6700\u65b056\u5dfb\u767a\u58f2\u3000\u57fa\u5c71\u753a\u51fa\u8eab\u30fb\u539f\u6cf0\u4e45\u3055\u3093\u306e\u4eba\u6c17\u6f2b\u753b |url=http://www.saga-s.co.jp/articles/-/455822 |website=Saga Shimbun |accessdate=November 21, 2019 |language=ja |date=November 19, 2019}}</ref> ''Kingdom'' was the 3rd best selling manga in 2019.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Loo |first1=Egan |title=Top-Selling Manga in Japan by Series: 2019 |url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2019-11-27/top-selling-manga-in-japan-by-series-2019/.153758 |website=[[Anime News Network]] |accessdate=November 28, 2019 |date=November 27, 2019}}</ref>\n\n''Kingdom'' was the grand prize winner for the [[Tezuka Osamu Cultural Prize]] in 2013 with one judge commenting, \"I can't remember the last time I read nearly 30 volumes (of a manga title) in a row feeling this excited.\"<ref>{{cite web|title=Tezuka Osamu Prize Winners |publisher=[[Asahi Shimbun]] |url=http://ajw.asahi.com/article/cool_japan/style/AJ201305090011 |accessdate=April 28, 2014 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140429185007/http://ajw.asahi.com/article/cool_japan/style/AJ201305090011 |archivedate=April 29, 2014 }}</ref> In 2019, ''Kingdom'' ranked 1st on the 19th \"Book of the Year\" list by ''Da Vinci'' magazine.<ref>{{cite web |author1=Rafael Antonio Pineda |title=Kingdom Manga Tops Da Vinci Ranking |url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2019-12-06/kingdom-manga-tops-da-vinci-ranking/.154037 |website=[[Anime News Network]] |accessdate=December 6, 2019 |date=December 6, 2019}}</ref>\n\nThe manga earned a Guinness World Record on December 12, 2012 for Manga written by the most people. The record was due to its \"Social Kingdom\" campaign in which fans and other artists were given the task of redrawing the entire 26th volume. Participants included manga creators [[Eiichiro Oda]] (''[[One Piece]]''), [[Masashi Kishimoto]] (''[[Naruto]]''), [[Hirohiko Araki]] (''[[JoJo's Bizarre Adventure]]''), as well as voice actors and fans.<ref>{{cite web|title=Kingdom wins Guinness World Record |publisher=[[Asahi Shimbun]] |url=http://ajw.asahi.com/article/cool_japan/anime_news/AJ201212310022 |accessdate=April 28, 2014 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140429201955/http://ajw.asahi.com/article/cool_japan/anime_news/AJ201212310022 |archivedate=April 29, 2014 }}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{Official website|http://www9.nhk.or.jp/anime/kingdom/|Official anime website}} {{in lang|ja}}\n* {{Ann|manga|11117|Kingdom}}\n\n{{Series in Weekly Young Jump}}\n{{Weekly Young Jump - 2000\u20132009}}\n{{Tezuka Osamu Cultural Prize}}\n{{Pierrot (company)}}\n{{Studio Signpost}}\n\n[[Category:2012 anime television series]]\n[[Category:2013 anime television series]]\n[[Category:2020 anime television series]]\n[[Category:Upcoming anime television series]]\n[[Category:Adventure anime and manga]]\n[[Category:Anime series based on manga]]\n[[Category:Funimation]]\n[[Category:Historical anime and manga]]\n[[Category:Manga adapted into films]]\n[[Category:NHK shows]]\n[[Category:Pierrot (company)]]\n[[Category:Seinen manga]]\n[[Category:Shueisha franchises]]\n[[Category:Shueisha manga]]\n[[Category:Studio Signpost]]\n[[Category:Television series set in the Zhou dynasty]]\n", "name_user": "Aerkdude", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eCharacters", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kingdom_(manga)"}
{"title_page": "Yinchuan Helanshan F.C.", "text_new": "{{Infobox football club |\n  clubname = Yinchuan Helanshan<br />Y\u00ednchu\u0101n H\u00e8l\u00e1nsh\u0101n<br />\u94f6\u5ddd\u8d3a\u5170\u5c71 |\n  image    = Yinchuan Helanshan FC logo2.png |\n  fullname = Yinchuan Helanshan Football Club<br />\u94f6\u5ddd\u8d3a\u5170\u5c71\u8db3\u7403\u4ff1\u4e50\u90e8|\n  nickname = |\n  founded  = {{Start date and age|2013|07|17|df=y}}|\ndissolved=2020|\n  ground   = [[Helan Mountain Stadium]], [[Yinchuan]]|\n  capacity = 39,872|\n  owner    = Yinchuan Sports Federation |\n  chairman = Xu Jun |\n  manager  = [[Zhao Changhong]]|\n  league   = [[China League Two]]|\n  season   = [[2019 China League Two|2019]]|\n  position = League Two, 10th|\n  pattern_la1=_whitecuffpiping|pattern_b1=_vneckwhite|pattern_ra1=_whitecuffpiping|pattern_so1= |\n  leftarm1=FF0000|body1=FF0000|rightarm1=FF0000|shorts1=FF0000|socks1=FF0000 |\n  pattern_la2=_blackcuffpiping|pattern_b2=_vneck|pattern_ra2=_blackcuffpiping|pattern_so2= |\n  leftarm2=B1FB17|body2=B1FB17|rightarm2=B1FB17|shorts2=B1FB17|socks2=B1FB17 |\n}}\n\n'''Yinchuan Helanshan Football Club''' is an [[association football]] club based in [[Yinchuan]], [[Ningxia]], [[China]]. The [[Helan Mountain Stadium]] is their home venue.\n\n==History==\nYinchuan Helanshan F.C. was established on 17 July 2013 by Yinchuan Sports Federation.<ref>[http://sports.163.com/13/1129/19/9ESE054N00051C8U.html \u5b81\u590f\u8d3a\u5170\u5c71\u8db3\u7403\u4ff1\u4e50\u90e8\u6b63\u5f0f\u4eae\u76f8] ports.163.com 2013-11-29 Retrieved 2016-04-08</ref><ref>[http://www.fa.org.cn/news/clb/2015-07-30/480599_7.html 2015\u4e2d\u4e59\u8054\u8d5b\u94f6\u5ddd\u8d3a\u5170\u5c71\u8db3\u7403\u4ff1\u4e50\u90e8\u7b80\u4ecb] fa.org.cn 2015-07-30 Retrieved 2016-04-08</ref>\n\nYinchuan Helanshan F.C. was disqualified for [[2020 China League Two]] on February 4, 2020 due to its failure to hand the salary and bonus confirmation form in time.<ref>{{cite news |title=\u4e2d\u56fd\u8db3\u534f\uff1a3\u652f\u4e2d\u75326\u652f\u4e2d\u4e59\u7403\u961f\u672a\u63d0\u4ea4\u5de5\u8d44\u5956\u91d1\u786e\u8ba4\u8868 |url=http://sports.xinhuanet.com/c/2020-02/04/c_1125530560.htm}}</ref>\n\n==Name changes==\n{| class=\"wikitable\" border=\"1\" width=70%\n|-\n! Year\n! Owner\n! Club name\n! Sponsored team name\n|-\n| 2013\u201315\n|rowspan=\"2\"| Yinchuan Sports Federation\n|rowspan=\"4\"| Yinchuan Helanshan Football Club\n|Ningxia Qupper (\u5b81\u590f\u675e\u52a8\u529b)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://news.sina.com.cn/c/2013-11-30/121028854629.shtml|title=\u8d3a\u5170\u5c71\u8db3\u7403\u4ff1\u4e50\u90e8\u9ad8\u8c03\u4eae\u76f8|publisher=Sina|date=30 November 2013|accessdate=12 April 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n| 2016 \n|rowspan=\"2\"| Ningxia Mountain & Sea (\u5b81\u590f\u5c71\u5c7f\u6d77)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://sports.xinmin.cn/2016/03/31/29764669.html|title=\u5b81\u590f\u5c71\u5c7f\u6d77\u8db3\u7403\u961f\u4e3e\u884c\u7403\u8ff7\u5a92\u4f53\u89c1\u9762\u4f1a|publisher=Xinmin Net|date=31 March 2016|accessdate=12 April 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n|2017\u20132018\n|Shenzhen Sea Elf Jewel Co. Ltd. (90%)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sport.org.cn/xhgg/2017/0111/141522.html|title=\u5173\u4e8e\u94f6\u5ddd\u8d3a\u5170\u5c71\u8db3\u7403\u4ff1\u4e50\u90e8\u6709\u9650\u516c\u53f8\u91cd\u8981\u80a1\u6743\u8f6c\u8ba9\u7684\u516c\u793a|publisher=Sports.org.cn|date=11 January 2017|accessdate=12 April 2018}}</ref><br />Yinchuan Sports Federation (10%)\n|-\n|2019\u2013\n|Yinchuan Sports Federation<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.dongqiudi.com/archive/875587.html|title=\u5173\u4e8e\u5b81\u590f\u5c71\u5c7f\u6d77\u9000\u51fa2019\u4e2d\u4e59\u8db3\u7403\u804c\u4e1a\u8054\u8d5b\u7684\u516c\u544a|work=Dongqiudi.com|date=2018-12-12|accessdate=2018-12-12|language=zh}}</ref>\n|Ningxia Fiery Phoenix (\u5b81\u590f\u706b\u51e4\u51f0)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://sports.sina.com.cn/china/b/2019-01-22/doc-ihqfskcn9537838.shtml|title=\u4e2d\u4e59\u5b81\u590f\u5c71\u5c7f\u6d77\u5b98\u5ba3\u6539\u540d\u706b\u51e4\u51f0 