{"title_page": "Netcomics", "text_new": "{{Notability|Companies|date=January 2010}}\n{{Infobox publisher\n| name         = NETCOMICS\n| image        = \n| caption      = \n| parent       = \n| status       = \n| traded_as    = \n| predecessor  = \n| founded      = 2005\n| founder      = Heewoon Chung\n| successor    = \n| country      = {{USA}}\n| headquarters = Los Angeles, California\n| distribution = [[Diamond Book Distributors]]<ref>[http://www.diamondbookdistributors.com/default.asp?t=2&m=1&c=53&s=660 Our Publishers]</ref>\n| keypeople    = \n| publications = [[manga]], <br /> [[manhwa]]\n| topics       = \n| genre        = [[Boy's Love]], Romance, Action\n| imprints     = \n| revenue      = \n| owner        = Heewoon Chung \n| numemployees = \n| website      = {{URL|www.netcomics.com}}\n}}\n\n'''NETCOMICS''' is a publisher of [[manhwa]], [[webtoons]], [[webcomics]], [[digital comics]], and [[manga]] [https://yattatachi.com/legal-online-manga-sites in] the United States, based in Los Angeles, CA, contributing to the [[Korean Wave]]. South Korean publisher [[Ecomix]] Media Company created NETCOMICS, with the first titles appearing in the first quarter of 2006.<ref>Cha, Kai-Ming. \"[http://www.netcomics.com/news/press_release.htm?uid=7 The Koreans Are Coming: NETCOMICS Brings Manhwa to U.S.: PW].\" Netcomics. December 6, 2005. Retrieved on December 9, 2011.</ref>\n\nNETCOMICS served as a distributor for some titles by manga publisher [[Aurora Publishing (United States)|Aurora Publishing]] until Aurora's closure in April 2010.<ref>http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2010-04-09/netcomics-to-remove-aurora-manga-on-april-14</ref>\n\nThey offer a huge variety of English titles that can be either rented or purchased on their homepage or app.[https://bookriot.com/2018/10/25/best-manga-reader-sites-and-apps/]\n\nIn particular, next to their Korean titles, their international outreach is significant.[https://animespiegel.de/blickpunkt-manga-legal-online-lesen/]\n\nBy offering several popular genres such as Boys Love, Romance, Drama, Fantasy, Comedy, Sci-Fi, Thriller, and Action, they compile a huge collection of popular titles.[https://www.netcomics.com/genre]\n\n<br />\n\n==Titles==\n*''[[0/6]]'' by [[Youjung Lee]]\n*''AEGIS'' by Jinha Yoo\n*''[[Dining Bar Akira]]'' by Tomoko Yamashita\n*''[[The Great Catsby]]'' by [[Doha Kang]]\n*''[[Let's Be Perverts]]'' by [[Youjung Lee]]\n*''[[Let Dai]]'' by Sooyeon Won\n*''[[Operation Liberate Men]]'' by [[Mira Lee]]\n*''[[Totally Captivated (manhwa)]]'' by Hajin Yoo\n*''[[X Diary]]'' by Toma\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Portal|New Jersey|Comics|Anime and manga}}\n* [http://www.netcomics.com/ Official Site]\n\n[[Category:Manga distributors]]\n[[Category:Manhwa distributors]]\n\n\n{{manga-stub}}\n{{Manhwa-stub}}\n{{US-publish-company-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Notability|Companies|date=January 2010}}\n{{Infobox publisher\n| name         = NETCOMICS\n| image        = \n| caption      = \n| parent       = \n| status       = \n| traded_as    = \n| predecessor  = \n| founded      = 2005\n| founder      = Heewoon Chung\n| successor    = \n| country      = {{USA}}\n| headquarters = Los Angeles, California\n| distribution = [[Diamond Book Distributors]]<ref>[http://www.diamondbookdistributors.com/default.asp?t=2&m=1&c=53&s=660 Our Publishers]</ref>\n| keypeople    = \n| publications = [[manga]], <br /> [[manhwa]]\n| topics       = \n| genre        = [[Boy's Love]], Romance, Action\n| imprints     = \n| revenue      = \n| owner        = Heewoon Chung \n| numemployees = \n| website      = {{URL|www.netcomics.com}}\n}}\n\n'''NETCOMICS''' is a publisher of [[manhwa]], [[webtoons]], [[webcomics]], [[digital comics]], and [[manga]] [https://yattatachi.com/legal-online-manga-sites in] the United States, based in Los Angeles, CA, contributing to the [[Korean Wave]]. South Korean publisher [[Ecomix]] Media Company created NETCOMICS, with the first titles appearing in the first quarter of 2006.<ref>Cha, Kai-Ming. \"[http://www.netcomics.com/news/press_release.htm?uid=7 The Koreans Are Coming: NETCOMICS Brings Manhwa to U.S.: PW].\" Netcomics. December 6, 2005. Retrieved on December 9, 2011.</ref>\n\nNETCOMICS served as a distributor for some titles by manga publisher [[Aurora Publishing (United States)|Aurora Publishing]] until Aurora's closure in April 2010.<ref>http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2010-04-09/netcomics-to-remove-aurora-manga-on-april-14</ref>\n\nThey offer a huge variety of English titles that can be either rented or purchased on their homepage or app.[https://bookriot.com/2018/10/25/best-manga-reader-sites-and-apps/]\n\nIn particular, next to their Korean titles, their international outreach is significant.[https://animespiegel.de/blickpunkt-manga-legal-online-lesen/]\n\nBy offering several popular genres such as Boys Love, Romance, Drama, Fantasy, Comedy, Sci-Fi, Thriller, and Action they compile a huge collection of popular titles.[https://www.netcomics.com/genre]\n\n<br />\n\n==Titles==\n*''[[0/6]]'' by [[Youjung Lee]]\n*''AEGIS'' by Jinha Yoo\n*''[[Dining Bar Akira]]'' by Tomoko Yamashita\n*''[[The Great Catsby]]'' by [[Doha Kang]]\n*''[[Let's Be Perverts]]'' by [[Youjung Lee]]\n*''[[Let Dai]]'' by Sooyeon Won\n*''[[Operation Liberate Men]]'' by [[Mira Lee]]\n*''[[Totally Captivated (manhwa)]]'' by Hajin Yoo\n*''[[X Diary]]'' by Toma\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Portal|New Jersey|Comics|Anime and manga}}\n* [http://www.netcomics.com/ Official Site]\n\n[[Category:Manga distributors]]\n[[Category:Manhwa distributors]]\n\n\n{{manga-stub}}\n{{Manhwa-stub}}\n{{US-publish-company-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Maria97531", "label": "safe", "comment": "grammar correction", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Netcomics"}
